Package info.kgeorgiy.ja.bondarev.implementor

Class Implementor

java.lang.Object
info.kgeorgiy.ja.bondarev.implementor.Implementor
All Implemented Interfaces:
Impler, JarImpler
public class Implementor extends Object implements Impler, JarImpler
Class that implements the Impler and JarImpler interfaces. Supports calling the JarImpler.implementJar(Class, Path) method by the main method.

  • Method Details

    • main

      public static void main(String[] args)
      The main function is used to generate a jar file with the implementation of the passed descriptor.It takes the string name of the interface descriptor and the path of the jar file and calls the implementJar(Class, Path) method. If the passed data is incorrect or the implementJar(Class, Path) method will fail with an exception, the function will display a corresponding message in System.err.
      Parameters:
      args - command line arguments. -jar is expected as the first argument, the second and third arguments are the interface descriptor and the path to the jar file, respectively.

    • implementJar

      public void implementJar(Class<?> token, Path jarFile) throws ImplerException
      Create jar file of empty implementation of the passed interface and save it to .jar file.
      Specified by:
      implementJar in interface JarImpler
      Parameters:
      token - type token to create implementation for.
      jarFile - target .jar file.
      Throws:
      ImplerException - if
      • tryCreateDirectories(Path) from jarFile throw it
      • jarFile has a parent and Files.createTempDirectory(Path, String, FileAttribute[]) from jarFile throw IOException or SecurityException
      • tryDeleteDirectory(Path) throws IOException from temporary directory
      • implement(Class, Path) throws ImplerException
      • compileClass(Path, Class) return code of generated class not equal to 0
      • writeJar(Class, Path, Path) from token temporary path and jarFile throws it
      See Also:
      • tryCreateDirectories(Path)
      • Files.createTempDirectory(Path, String, FileAttribute[])
      • tryDeleteDirectory(Path)
      • implement(Class, Path)
      • compileClass(Path, Class)
      • writeJar(Class, Path, Path)

    • generateCode

      private void generateCode(Class<?> token, StringBuilder code)
      Generates class code that implements the passed interface and writes it to StringBuilder. Generation includes: package generation, class header generation and class body generation. Code is generated in Kernighan style.
      Parameters:
      token - descriptor of interface
      code - StringBuilder to generating
      See Also:
      • generatePackage(Class, StringBuilder)
      • generateClassHeader(Class, StringBuilder)
      • generateMethods(Class, StringBuilder)

    • generatePackage

      private void generatePackage(Class<?> token, StringBuilder code)
      Generates a package class from the given interface. This function does not generate anything if the packet of the passed descriptor is null or empty. Generated code writes to passed StringBuilder. The generated packet is equal to the packets of the passed descriptor. An empty line is generated after the packet.
      Parameters:
      token - descriptor of interface
      code - StringBuilder to generating

    • generateClassHeader

      private void generateClassHeader(Class<?> token, StringBuilder code)
      Generates a public class header from the given interface. Generated code writes to passed StringBuilder. The name of generated class header is InterfaceName + Impl.
      Parameters:
      token - descriptor of interface
      code - StringBuilder to generating

      private void generateMethods(Class<?> token, StringBuilder code)

    • generateMethod

      private void generateMethod(Method method, StringBuilder code)
      Generate code of passed method to StringBuilder. Code is generated in Kernighan style, method modifiers are generated completely excluding the ABSTRACT and TRANSIENT modifiers. The return value and parameter types are generated in the canonical name. The argument names are taken from the descriptor. The generateReturnValue(Class) method is used to generate the default implementation.
      Parameters:
      method - descriptor of method that will be generated.
      code - StringBuilder to generating
      See Also:
      • generateReturnValue(Class)

    • generateReturnValue

      private String generateReturnValue(Class<?> clazz)
      Return string of default return value by descriptor.
      Parameters:
      clazz - descriptor of return value
      Returns:
      a string displaying the default value for the passed descriptor
